    "question_id" : 27454025,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It turns out Java does not accept a bare Date value as DateTime. Using LocalDate instead of LocalDateTime solves the issue:</p>\n\n<pre><code>DateTimeFormatter formatter = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(\"yyyyMMdd\");\nLocalDate dt = LocalDate.parse(\"20140218\", formatter);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 216162,
